<span class="name"><a name="13358"></a></span><span class="postdetails">#1:&nbsp;<font color=black><b>My first experience being summoned</b> Author:&nbsp;<b>brakeformezz</b>,&nbsp;</font></span><span class="postdetails"><font color=black></font></span>
<a href="viewtopic.php?p=13358#13358"><img src="templates/subSilver/images/icon_minipost.gif" width="12" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" border="0" /></a><span class="postdetails"><font color=black>Posted: Wed Dec 17, 2003 4:38 pm</font><span class="gen"><br>
</td></tr>
<tr><td class="printline">
<span class="postbody">Our guild did a Kael raid recently to work on faction (yeah, I heard some classes can't cast their way to indifferent or amiable with almost any group they meet, but I got to group with some people I hadn't grouped with in a while, since they play and level more than I, so I thought it would be fun).
<br />

<br />
We split the debuffing between the other chanter, a shaman, and myself.  The other chanter tashed, the shaman slowed, and I incapacitated.  In retrospect, perhaps it would have been better for me to tash, since the other chanter was higher level and would have had fewer resists on his debuffs.  Once we got to the arena, the giants were quite red to me.
<br />

<br />
Usually my debuff would land, but on some of the mobs it got resisted.  I cast it again on a couple of them, after waiting a few seconds for other people to deal more damage, and didn't get aggro.
<br />

<br />
So I got a bit stubborn and bold on one mob, and when it got resisted on the first and second cast, thought "oh, I can give it one more go."  It got resisted again.
<br />

<br />
Suddenly a giant spawned in front of me!  Aaaagh!  How did that happen?
<br />

<br />
And where are the other casters?
<br />

<br />
It was only after I got away from it (still full health, oh I am so fleet of foot and my brave pet is so tauntacious) that I saw the text in the chat of "You shall not escape me, debuffing chanter!"
<br />

<br />
I'd never been summoned before, quite an invigorating experience.  Certainly more invigorating for me than for the cleric who got flattened after he aggroed.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
</td></tr>
<br />
<table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
<tr><td class="printline">
<span class="name"><a name="14618"></a></span><span class="postdetails">#2:&nbsp;<font color=black><b></b> Author:&nbsp;<b>VadeZar</b>,&nbsp;</font></span><span class="postdetails"><font color=black></font></span>
<a href="viewtopic.php?p=14618#14618"><img src="templates/subSilver/images/icon_minipost.gif" width="12" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" border="0" /></a><span class="postdetails"><font color=black>Posted: Fri Dec 26, 2003 5:09 pm</font><span class="gen"><br>
</td></tr>
<tr><td class="printline">
<span class="postbody">Being summoned isn't too cool at all is it.
<br />

<br />
But later on you get used to it, generally in a EXP group I get summoned regularly (I know how to keep from getting aggro if I want too, tho).
<br />

<br />
This is my most memorable memory of a summoning mob.  One day I was playing my Ranger and saw a named goblin up in Frontieer Mountains, so I go over to kill it out of curiousity.  (I've never seen this golbin before from my FM rampages of the past)
<br />

<br />
Damn, thing hits pretty hard.  Might actually have to back off and heal a bit.  Start to back up, and you've been summoned!  Oh shit.  This is NOT cool.  I've died in this zone and it took me an entire evening to find my corpse once.
<br />

<br />
I got summoned around 20 times before I finally made it to the DL zone line.  The worst part was - I snared the goblin.  So he wasn't really moving that fast and slowed my progress a whole lot.  It really pisses you off when you get summoned feet away from the zone line.  But I lived.  Somehow.  =)</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
</td></tr>
<br />
