<span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">This is my most memorable memory of a summoning mob. One day I was playing my Ranger and saw a named goblin up in Frontieer Mountains, so I go over to kill it out of curiousity. (I've never seen this golbin before from my FM rampages of the past)</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
I know what goblin you are talking about, the one for the Shaman Cudgel quest.  I remember feeling uber when I got my Necro to 51 (you know the 1k DoT spells and whatnot) and my druid friend (55 atm) seen him on track, so we go to him me my 51 mage friend who I leveled up with from 44+ duoing and this Druid friend of ours.
<br />

<br />
He is immune to runspeed changes IIRC, because I tried to Darkness him and the Druid tried to Ensnare him.  That wasn't the worse.  I then tried to fear it (Immune to Fear type spells also <img src="images/smiles/icon_sad.gif" alt="icon_sad.gif" border="0" />) and after Mage nuked it it all went downhill.  Summon, turned into a goblin and kill... All of us.  Worse experience IMO.  Took forever to find the corpses and had to beg a level 60 Cleric from the Uberguild of the server (PoP wasn't released yet) to go there to rez us.  So hard to see Goblin corpses on the rocks when they sink in due to geometry.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
</td></tr>
