<tr><td class="printline">
<span class="postbody">Actually, my first experience with summoning mobs wasn't with me getting summoned, but rather with a friend.  I was about level 30 or so and was doing something odd like camping a named owlbear for a drop of some sort.  This high-level druid friend (she was probably 59 or so, but at the time she might as well have been 80, as the higher levels were impossible for me to even imagine) decided to help me out.  Well, I'd never seen a summoning mob before.  My friend aggroed the named mob, then she kept running up to me and disappearing, running up to me and disappearing, running up to me and disappearing...all the while her hit points are dropping, and I'm completely confused.  Eventually it killed her.  I feel really bad now because if we had known what was happening, my husband could have invited her into a group and ported her somewhere before she died.
<br />

<br />
My friend was really chagrined at being killed by (I think) a light blue con.  She quit EQ maybe a month later.  I hope it wasn't because of that, but I always have felt that the experience kind of broke her EQ spirit.   <img src="images/smiles/icon_sad.gif" alt="icon_sad.gif" border="0" /></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
</td></tr>
